ide to Breeds and Welfare''. London:  David and Charles Publishing.</ref--->\n\n<ref name=janet>{{citation|title= The Encyclopedia of Historic and Endangered Livestock and Poultry Breeds|author=Janet Vorwald Dohner|publisher=[[Yale University Press]]|year= 2001|isbn=0-300-08880-9|pages=421\u2013423}}</ref>\n\n<!---<ref name=roy>{{citation|title=Poultry Breeding and Genetics|author =Roy D. Crawford|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|year=1990|isbn=0-444-88557-9}}. Pages 1033\u20131034.</ref>--->\n\n<ref name=sid>Sidney Hubert Lewer (1924). ''British Poultry and Poultry Keeping''. London: Feathered World.</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n\n* Thomas William Sturges (1911). [https://archive.org/details/poultrymanualcom00stur ''The Poultry Manual: A Complete Guide for the Breeder and Exhibitor]'', second edition. London: Macdonald and Evans.\n\n{{British livestock|R.4}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dorking (Chicken)}}\n[[Category:Conservation Priority Breeds of the Livestock Conservancy]]\n[[Category:Chicken breeds]]\n[[Category:Chicken breeds originating in England]]\n[[Category:Animal breeds on the RBST Watchlist]]\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "Commemmoration->Commemoration -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dorking_chicken"}
{"title_page": "Yu (kana)", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox kana\n|Hiragana image =Japanese Hiragana kyokashotai YU.png\n|Katakana image = Japanese Katakana YU.png\n|Transliteration = yu\n|Hiragana Manyogana = \u7531\n|Katakana Manyogana = \u7531\n|Braille = [[File:Japanese Yu Braille.svg|32px|\u282c]]\n|Unicode = U+3086, U+30E6\n|flag1=9|flag2=1\n|Footnotes = \n|Spelling=\u5f13\u77e2\u306e\u30e6 [[Bow (weapon)|Yumiya]] no \"yu\"\n}}\n\n{{kana gojuon sidebar}}\n\n'''\u3086''', in [[hiragana]], or '''\u30e6''' in [[katakana]], is one of the Japanese [[kana]], which each represent one [[Mora (linguistics)|mora]]. Both are written in two strokes and represent {{IPA|[ju\u034d]}}.\n\nWhen small and preceded by an -i kana, this kana represents not a separate sound but a modification of that of another (see [[y\u014don]]).<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kE3RAgAAQBAJ|chapter=Contracted sounds|title=Japanese Hiragana: An Introductory Japanese Language Workbook|author=Jim Gleeson|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|year=2013|isbn=9781462913978}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Forms\n![[R\u014dmaji]]\n![[Hiragana]]\n![[Katakana]]\n|-bbvhhvvvbvg\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Normal ''y-''<br>(\u3084\u884c ''ya-gy\u014d'')\n|''yu''\n|\u3086\n|\u30e6\n|-\n|''yuu''<br>''y\u016b''\n|\u3086\u3046, \u3086\u3045<br>\u3086\u30fc\n|\u30e6\u30a6, \u30e6\u30a5<br>\u30e6\u30fc\n|}\n\n==Stroke order==\n{|\n|-\n| [[File:Hiragana \u3086 stroke order animation.gif|thumb|upright|alt=Stroke order in writing \u3086|Stroke order in writing \u3086]]\n| [[File:Katakana \u30e6 stroke order animation.gif|thumb|upright|alt=Stroke order in writing \u30e6|Stroke order in writing \u30e6]]\n|}\n\n[[Image:\u3086-bw.png|thumb|none|280x60px|Stroke order in writing \u3086]]\n[[Image:\u30e6-bw.png|thumb|none|280x60px|Stroke order in writing \u30e6]]\n\n==Other representations==\n* [[Character encoding|Computer encodings]]\n{{charmap\n|3086|name1=Hiragana Letter Yu\n|30E6|name2=Katakana Letter Yu\n|FF95|name3=Half