{"title_page": "Wellington Bay", "text_new": "{{Infobox body of water\n|name= Wellington Bay\n|image=\n|caption =\n|location= [[Dease Strait]]\n|coords= {{coord|69.37|-106.50|region:CA-NU_type:waterbody_scale:500000|display=inline,title|name=Wellington Bay}}\n|rivers= Ekalluk River<br />Halovik River<br />Lauchlan River<br />Paliryuak River\n|oceans=\n|countries= [[Canada]]\n|length=\n|width=\n|area=\n|cities= Uninhabited\n|references=\n}}\n'''Wellington Bay'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topozone.com/map.asp?lon=-106.5&lat=69.375|title=Natural Resources Canada WELLINGTON BAY Quad, Nunavut, Topographic Map|publisher=topozone.com|accessdate=2008-10-11}}</ref> is an [[Arctic]] waterway in [[Kitikmeot Region, Nunavut|Kitikmeot Region]], [[Nunavut]], [[Canada]]. It is located in [[Dease Strait]], off southern [[Victoria Island (Canada)|Victoria Island]]. It is northwest of the community of [[Cambridge Bay, Nunavut|Cambridge Bay]].\n\nIt is one of [[Wellington (disambiguation)#Canada|several Canadian landforms]] named in honor of [[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington]].\n\n==Geography==\nThere are several small islands within the bay. Several rivers flow into it including the [[Ekalluk River]], [[Halovik River]], [[Lauchlan River]], and [[Paliryuak River]].<ref name=\"Char\">{{cite web|url=http://google.com/search?q=cache:gwURKpG_RoQJ:www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/Library/284796.pdf+%22wellington+bay%22+cambridge&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=us&client=firefox-a|title=Cambridge Bay Arctic Char|date=2004|work=Stock Status Report 2004/010|publisher=dfo-mpo.gc.ca|pages=3|accessdate=2009-05-06}}</ref>\n\n==Fauna==\nCommerciality fishing activities include [[Arctic char]].<ref name=\"Char\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Bays of Nunavut}}\n\n[[Category:Bays of Kitikmeot Region]]\n[[Category:Victoria Island (Canada)]]\n\n\n{{KitikmeotNU-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox body of water\n|name= Wellington Bay\n|image=\n|caption =\n|location= [[Dease Strait]]\n|coords= {{coord|69.37|-106.50|region:CA-NU_type:waterbody_scale:500000|display=inline,title|name=Wellington Bay}}\n|rivers= Ekalluk River<br />Halovik River<br />Lauchlan River<br />Paliryuak River\n|oceans=\n|countries= [[Canada]]\n|length=\n|width=\n|area=\n|cities= Uninhabited\n|references=\n}}\n'''Wellington Bay'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topozone.com/map.asp?lon=-106.5&lat=69.375|title=Natural Resources Canada WELLINGTON BAY Quad, Nunavut, Topographic Map|publisher=topozone.com|accessdate=2008-10-11}}</ref> is an [[Arctic]] waterway in [[Kitikmeot Region, Nunavut|Kitikmeot Region]], [[Nunavut]], [[Canada]]. It is located in [[Dease Strait]], off southern [[Victoria Island (Canada)|Victoria Island]]. It is northwest of the community of [[Cambridge Bay, Nunavut|Cambridge Bay]].\n\nIt is one of [[Wellington (disambiguation)#Canada|several Canadian landforms]] named in honor of [[Arthur Wellesley, 1st Duke of Wellington]].\n\n==Geography==\nThere are several small islands within the bay. Several rivers flow into it including the [[Ekalluk River]], [[Halovik River]], [[Lauchlan River]], and [[Paliryuak River]].<ref name=\"Char\">{{cite web|url=http://google.com/search?q=cache:gwURKpG_RoQJ:www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/Library/284796.pdf+%22wellington+bay%22+cambridge&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=us&client=firefox-a|title=Cambridge Bay Arctic Char|date=2004|work=Stock Status Report 2004/010|publisher=dfo-mpo.gc.ca|pages=3|accessdate=2009-05-06}}</ref>\n\n==Fauna==\nCommercialty fishing activities include [[Arctic char]].<ref name=\"Char\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Bays of Nunavut}}\n\n[[Category:Bays of Kitikmeot Region]]\n[[Category:Victoria Island (Canada)]]\n\n\n{{KitikmeotNU-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "Commercialty->Commerciality -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wellington_Bay"}
